<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,632,1068]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName authority="Poche, 1926" authorityName="Poche" authorityYear="1926" box="[151,486,632,658]" class="Trematoda" family="Mesometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">
Mesometridae Poche, 
<number box="[425,486,632,658]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1926.0">1926</number>
</taxonomicName>
is a small trematode family, parasitizing the digestive tract of marine teleost fishes. Historically, the systematic position and relationships of this family have long been in dispute (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Szidat" box="[151,292,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Szidat, L. (1936) Uber Entwicklungsgeschichte und den ersten Zwischenwirt von Paramphistomum cervi Zeder 1790 aus dem Magen von Wiederkauern. Zeitschrift fur Parasitenkunde, 9, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="1936">
Szidat 
<number box="[233,292,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1936.0">1936</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Skrjabin" box="[316,488,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Skrjabin, K. I. (1949) trematodes of animal and man. Principles of trematodology. volume 3. House Asci. USSR. Moscow, Leningrad, 468 pp. (In Russian)" type="book" year="1949">
Skrjabin 
<number box="[425,488,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1949.0">1949</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Jousson 
<emphasis box="[603,663,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[671,734,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1957.0">1957</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Holliman" box="[747,930,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Holliman, R. B. (1961) Larval trematodes from the Apalachee Bay area, Florida, with a checklist of known marine cercariae arranged in a key to their superfamilies. Tulane Studies in Zoology, 9, 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1961">
Holliman 
<number box="[867,930,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yamaguti" box="[943,1128,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Yamaguti, S. (1971) Synopsis of digenetic trematodes of vertebrates 1. Tokyo: Keigaku Publishing Company, 1074 pp." type="book" year="1971">
Yamaguti 
<number box="[1065,1128,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bray" box="[1141,1269,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Bray, R. A. (1984) Some helminth parasites of marine fishes and cephalopods of South Africa: Aspidogastrea and the digenean families Bucephalidae, Haplosplanchnidae, Mesometridae and Fellodistomidae. Journal of Natural History, 18, 271 - 292. DOI: 10.1080 / 00222938400770211" type="journal article" year="1984">
Bray 
<number box="[1206,1269,706,732]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brooks" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Brooks, D. R., O'Grady, R. T. &amp; Glen, D. R. (1985) Phylogenetic analysis of the Digenea (Platyhelminthes: Cercomeria) with comments on their adaptive radiation. Canadian Journal of Zoology, 63, 411 - 443." type="journal article" year="1985">
Brooks 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[151,213,744,770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pearson" box="[226,388,744,770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Pearson, J. C. (1992) On the position of the digenean family Heronimidae: An enquiry into a cladistic classification of the Digenea. Systematic Parasitology, 21, 81 - 166. DOI: 10.1007 / BF 00010255" type="journal article" year="1992">
Pearson 
<number box="[326,388,744,770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb" box="[401,605,744,770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Cribb, T. H., Bray, R. A., Olson, P. D. &amp; Littlewood, D. T. J., 2003. Life cycle evolution in the Digenea: a new perspective from phylogeny. Advances in Parasitology, 54, 197 - 254. DOI: 10.1016 / S 0065 - 308 X (03) 54004 - 0" type="journal article" year="2003">
Cribb 
<emphasis box="[476,535,744,769]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[543,605,744,770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Olson 
<emphasis box="[696,756,744,769]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[764,827,744,770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2003.0">2003</number>
). In this family, the tegument is spined, the anterior region of the ventral surface or all of it, is concave, acting as an accessory attachment organ since the mucosal surface of the host is smooth (
<bibRefCitation author="Bartoli" box="[510,666,818,844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Bartoli, P. (1987) Caracteres adaptifs originaux des Digenes intestinaux de Sarpa salpa (Teleostei, Sparidae) et leur interpretation en termes d'evolution. Annales de Parasitologie Humaine et Comparee, 62, 542 - 576." type="journal article" year="1987">
Bartoli 
<number box="[603,666,818,844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the oral sucker is absent (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[1039,1287,818,844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Hall, K. A. &amp; Cribb T. H. (2000) The status of Petalocotyle Ozaki, 1934 (Digenea: Gyliauchenidae), including the description of two new species from acanthurid fishes in Queensland, Australia. Systematic Parasitology, 47, 145 - 156. DOI: 10.1023 / A: 1006448519956" type="journal article" year="2000">
Hall and Cribb 
<number box="[1224,1287,818,844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Cribb 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[151,213,856,882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2001.0">2001</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones" box="[226,480,856,882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Jones, A. &amp; Blair, D. (2005) Family Mesometridae Poche, 1926. In: Gibson, D. I., Jones, A. &amp; Bray, R. A (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Volume 2. CABI Publishing, Wallingford, U. K. pp 213 - 219." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Jones and Blair 
<number box="[417,480,856,882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the ventral sucker is absent, the cirrus sac is absent and the excretory system is reticular. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones" box="[263,533,893,919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Jones, A. &amp; Blair, D. (2005) Family Mesometridae Poche, 1926. In: Gibson, D. I., Jones, A. &amp; Bray, R. A (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Volume 2. CABI Publishing, Wallingford, U. K. pp 213 - 219." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Jones and Blair (
<number box="[463,525,893,919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
comprehensively reviewed the family, recognizing 
<number box="[1151,1166,893,919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
genera as valid within the family; 
<taxonomicName authority="Luhe, 1901" authorityName="Luhe" authorityYear="1901" box="[290,571,930,956]" class="Trematoda" family="Mesometridae" genus="Mesometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[290,424,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Mesometra</emphasis>
Luhe, 
<number box="[509,571,930,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1901.0">1901</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Luhe, 1901" authorityName="Luhe" authorityYear="1901" box="[585,889,930,956]" class="Trematoda" family="Mesometridae" genus="Centroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[585,743,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Centroderma</emphasis>
Luhe, 
<number box="[827,889,930,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1901.0">1901</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Poche, 1926" authorityName="Poche" authorityYear="1926" box="[903,1162,930,956]" class="Trematoda" family="Mesometridae" genus="Wardula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,1001,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Wardula</emphasis>
Poche, 
<number box="[1100,1162,930,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1926.0">1926</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bray, 1984" authorityName="Bray" authorityYear="1984" box="[1175,1385,930,956]" class="Trematoda" family="Mesometridae" genus="Elstia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1175,1245,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Elstia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bray" box="[1253,1385,930,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Bray, R. A. (1984) Some helminth parasites of marine fishes and cephalopods of South Africa: Aspidogastrea and the digenean families Bucephalidae, Haplosplanchnidae, Mesometridae and Fellodistomidae. Journal of Natural History, 18, 271 - 292. DOI: 10.1080 / 00222938400770211" type="journal article" year="1984">
Bray, 
<number box="[1325,1385,930,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jones et Blair, 2005" authorityName="Jones et Blair" authorityYear="2005" box="[151,552,968,994]" class="Trematoda" family="Mesometridae" genus="Parawardula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,307,968,993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Parawardula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jones" box="[314,552,968,994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Jones, A. &amp; Blair, D. (2005) Family Mesometridae Poche, 1926. In: Gibson, D. I., Jones, A. &amp; Bray, R. A (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Volume 2. CABI Publishing, Wallingford, U. K. pp 213 - 219." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Jones et Blair, 
<number box="[490,552,968,994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These genera are easily distinguished from each other by the professional keys given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones" box="[325,600,1005,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" refString="Jones, A. &amp; Blair, D. (2005) Family Mesometridae Poche, 1926. In: Gibson, D. I., Jones, A. &amp; Bray, R. A (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Volume 2. CABI Publishing, Wallingford, U. K. pp 213 - 219." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Jones and Blair (
<number box="[526,591,1005,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. To date, no other genera are added and the 
<number box="[1128,1143,1005,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
known genera comprise about 
<number box="[223,237,1042,1068]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="8.0">8</number>
species.
</paragraph>
